to set up roles in OneLake Security after the Mirrored database has been created.",MirrorSecuritySettings_Sync_Title:"Sync existing security roles from source",MirrorSecuritySettings_Sync_Description:"Mirror security roles from your source database. Fabric creates matching roles to keep permissions aligned.",MirrorSecuritySettings_Sync_InfoTitle:"Security roles will sync automatically",MirrorSecuritySettings_Sync_InfoDescription:"Syncing security roles from your source database automatically activates OneLake security. This controls access to your mirrored database.",MirrorAllButtonLabel:"Automatically mirror future tables",MirrorAllButtonDescription:"Any new tables added to the source will be replicated to the destination.",MirrorAllObjectTypeDescriptionPrefix:"Any new",MirrorAllObjectTypeDescriptionSuffix:"added to the source will be replicated to the destination.",CancelChangeData:"Cancel changes",CancelMountDataContent:"If you cancel now, you will lose all the unsaved mirroring configuration changes. Are you sure you want to cancel?",CancelCopyJobContent:"If you cancel now, you will lose all the unsaved copy job configuration changes. Are you sure you want to cancel?",ApplyChangesText:"Apply changes",MountAllDataDescription:"When enabled, all data updates in your external operational database will appear in your Mirrored database. That way, your Mirrored warehouse stays up-to-date. If not enabled, your new Mirrored warehouse won't include refreshed data. Instead it will be static.",MountAllDataUpdates:"Mirror all data updates",MountAllDataDescription2:"Mirroring data creates a replica of your external operational database. Your replica will be automatically refreshed anytime an update happens in the operational database. You can choose to Mirror all the data within the database, or just a portion.",ChooseDataForMounting:"Choose data",MirrorWizardHeaderInCreateMode:"New mirrored {0}",MirrorWizardHeaderInEditMode:"Mirrored {0}",MirrorPlaceholder_UnknownDatabase:"Unknown database",Mirror_SAP_Choose_Subtype:"Choose a type of SAP mirror to get started",Mirror_SAP_ShortCut_Path_title:"Shortcut path",Mirror_SAP_ShortCut_Path_description:"Please provide the path to the OneLake shortcut pointing to the ADLS container into which SAP Datasphere replicates your SAP data.",Mirror_SAP_ABAP_header:"Mirrored SAP Application",Mirror_SAP_ABAP_description:'This option replicates data directly from SAP applications like SAP ECC, SAP S/4HANA, SAP BW and others into Fabric. Before getting started with the replication, install and setup the "Mirrored SAP AddOn" on your SAP instance.',Mirror_SAP_Datasphere_header:"Mirrored SAP via SAP Datasphere",Mirror_SAP_Datasphere_Description:"This option replicates data from SAP applications using SAP Datasphere. To get started, set up a replication flow from your SAP instance into Azure Data Lake Gen2 in your SAP Datasphere tenant and connect the storage container to a mirrored database.",CreateMirroredDatabase:"Create mirrored database",SelectDataToMount:"Select data to mirror",MountGeneralErrorMessage:"Error happens. Please try again later.",InputRequiredFields:"Please input required fields.",ChooseADataSourceToGetStarted:"Choose a data source to get started",ChooseAConnectionToGetStarted:"Choose a {0} connection to get started",RefreshTablesAndSelections:"Refresh tables and selections",ColumnDataTypeUnsupported:"This table contains unsupported columns: {0}.\nThose columns will not be replicated.",MirrorWizardPageDescription_TablePageDescInEditMode:"Manage your mirroring configuration",InvalidMirror_TableCountExceedsLimit:"The selected table count of {0} exceeds the limit of {1}.",SourceConnectionError_GeneralPrefix:"The database cannot be mirrored to Fabric due to below error:",SourceConnectionError_IncorrectConnectionType:"This connection is not of type {0}.",SourceConnectionError_NotExist:"Failed to get source connection. Please check if the source connection exists and you have the permission.\nConnec